==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rampion
<hw>Ram"pi*on</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧m"p⟦icr⟧*⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>raiponce</ets>, Sp. <ets>ruiponce</ets>,
<ets>reponche</ets>, L. <ets>raperonzo</ets>, NL. <ets>rapuntium</ets>,
fr. L. <ets>rapum</ets>, <ets>rapa</ets>, a turnip, rape. Cf.
<er>Rape</er> a plant.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant
(<spn>Campanula Rapunculus</spn>) of the Bellflower family, with a
tuberous esculent root; -- also called
<altname>ramps</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The name is sometimes given to plants of the genus
<gen>Phyteuma</gen>, herbs of the Bellflower family, and to the American
evening primrose (<spn>⟦OE⟧nothera biennis</spn>), which has run wild in
some parts of Europe.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rampire</ent>⟦br⟧
